            . I am a <rs id="t18301028-120-viclabel675" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301028-120-victim1067 t18301028-120-viclabel675"></join>, and live at Stoke Newington. I was driving my wife in a cart across <placeName id="t18301028-120-crimeloc676">Newington-green</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18301028-120-crimeloc676" type="placeName" value="Newington-green"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18301028-120-crimeloc676" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301028-120-off673 t18301028-120-crimeloc676"></join>, on the 25th of July, towards Islington - there was a shawl laying between us both in the cart, and she had her hand upon it - there was no part of it out at the tail of the cart; I am positive it did not fall out - we sat with our faces towards the horse; the prisoner was driving some sheep - he came and put his hand through<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183010280059"></xptr>the rails at the back of the cart, and took out the shawl; I turned my head, and saw it in his hand - he ran away with it; I got down, and chased him some distance - he put the shawl into his hat, and ran off; I lost sight of him - I could not get clear of the sheep; this was on a Sunday afternoon; I saw him again when he was taken, and am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>JOHN VINN. I heard that two persons had been driving the sheep, and on the 7th of October one was taken - he said it was not him, it was the pieman, meaning the prisoner, and the prisoner was then taken.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. The prosecutor said I had a long brown coat on.</p>
               <p>MR. GANTLEY. No; I said a brown jacket.</p>
